b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Bing Image Creator is best suited for free DALL E 3 access, casual users, quick images, beginners, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Leonardo AI, meanwhile, shines for game assets, character design, concept art, custom styles, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2023, Bing Image Creator describes itself as \"Free DALL-E 3 powered image generator by Microsoft.\" Leonardo AI, established in 2022, positions itself as \"AI image platform with custom model training and game assets.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Leonardo AI** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 6.0), more features (9 vs 1), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Bing Image Creator is a poor choice — far from it. Bing Image Creator excels in its own right, particularly for free DALL E 3 access and casual users.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value generous free tier with 150 daily tokens, go with Leonardo AI. If completely free dall-e 3 access matters more to you, Bing Image Creator is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
